            "questionText": "In a photography studio, a circular studio lamp with radius $!$R_l$!$ is placed $!$d_l$!$ away from an opaque subject of diameter $!$D_s$!$. A backdrop is positioned $!$d_b$!$ behind the subject. Assuming all distances are measured from the corresponding centers, calculate the diameter of the umbra (complete shadow) cast on the backdrop. Please provide numerical values for $!$R_l$!$, $!$d_l$!$, $!$D_s$!$, and $!$d_b$!$.",
